        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 14 at 6:26PM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 625 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles north of Divide, or 15 miles southwest of Butte, moving
northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible. Localized flash flooding near and below steep
terrain is possible. Ponding on roadways and low-lying
areas is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Deer Lodge, Butte, Anaconda, Silver Bow, Walkerville, Warm Springs,
Galen, Gregson Hot Springs, West Valley, Nissler, Crackerville,
Racetrack, Lost Creek, Opportunity, Blossburg, Ramsay, Janney,
Newcomb, and Elliston.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 90 between mile markers 185 and 231.
Highway 12 Garrison to MacDonald Pass between mile markers 18 and
26.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
